om/Tournaments/Details/1944 |title=GEICO PBA World Series of Bowling VI |website=PBA.com |accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n! Event !! Airdate !! Preliminary rounds !! Final round !! Winner !! Runner-up\n|-\n| '''Cheetah Championship'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pba.com/Tournaments/FullStandings/2013 |title=PBA Cheetah Championship presented by PBA Bowling Challenge Mobile Game - Full Standings |website=PBA.com |accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| Dec 14\n| Oct 25, 30\n| Nov 2\n| Anthony Pepe, USA\n| Mika Koivuniemi, Finland\n|-\n| '''Viper Championship'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pba.com/Tournaments/FullStandings/2014 |title=PBA Viper Championship - Full Standings |website=PBA.com |accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| Dec 21\n| Oct 26, 30\n| Nov 2\n| Mika Koivuniemi, Finland\n| Connor Pickford, USA\n|-\n| '''Chameleon Championship'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pba.com/Tournaments/FullStandings/2017 |title=PBA Chameleon Championship - Full Standings |website=PBA.com |accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| Dec 28\n| Oct 27, 31\n| Nov 2\n| DJ Archer, USA\n| Ronnie Russell, USA\n|-\n| '''Scorpion Championship'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pba.com/Tournaments/FullStandings/2020 |title=PBA Scorpion Championship - Full Standings |website=PBA.com |accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| Jan 4\n| Oct 28, 31\n| Nov 2\n| [[Michael Haugen Jr.]], USA\n| Martin Larsen, Sweden\n|-\n| '''PBA World Championship'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pba.com/Tournaments/FullStandings/2021 |title=PBA World Championship - Full Standings |website=PBA.com |accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| Jan 11\n| Oct 25\u201331\n| ''Live''\n| Mike Fagan, USA\n| Wes Malott, USA\n|-\n|}\n\n===World Series of Bowling VII===\n'''Dates:'''  December 8\u201319, 2015<br>\n'''Location:''' [[Reno, Nevada]]\n\n'''Events:'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pba.com/Tournaments/Season/81 |title=PBA 2015 Season Schedule |website=PBA.com |accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref><ref