 Barrett Wins First PBA Tour Title in Scorpion Open |publisher=PBA |date=February 19, 2012 |accessdate=March 6, 2020 |url=http://news.pba.com/post/2012/2/19/Englande28099s-Dom-Barrett-Wins-First-PBA-Tour-Title-in-Scorpion-Open.aspx}}</ref>\n| Feb 19\n| Nov 7\n| Nov 19\n| [[Dominic Barrett]], England\n| Sean Rash, USA\n|-\n| '''Shark Open'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pba.com/Tournaments/FullStandings/1706 |title=GEICO Shark Open - Full Standings |website=PBA.com |accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n| Mar 4\n| Nov 8\n| Nov 19\n| Jason Belmonte, Australia\n| Chris Barnes, USA\n|-\n| '''PBA World Championship'''<ref>{{cite web |last=Vint |first=Bill |title=Finland's Osku Palermaa Becomes First International Player to Win PBA World Championship, First Two-Hander to Win PBA Major Title |publisher=PBA |date=January 15, 2012 |accessdate=March 6, 2020 |url=http://news.pba.com/post/2012/1/15/Finlande28099s-Osku-Palermaa-Becomes-First-International-Player-to-Win-PBA-World-Championship-First-Two-Hander-to-Win-PBA-Major-Title.aspx}}</ref>\n| Jan 15\n| Nov 5\u20138, 17\u201318\n| Nov 18\n| Osku Palermaa, Finland\n| Ryan Shafer, USA\n|-\n|}\n\n===World Series of Bowling IV===\n'''Dates:'''  November 3\u201311, 2012<br>\n'''Location:''' [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]]\n\n'''Events:'''<ref name=PBA-12-13>{{cite web |url=https://www.pba.com/Tournaments/Season/76 |title=PBA 2012-2013 Season Schedule |website=PBA.com |accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n! Event !! Airdate !! Preliminary rounds !! Final round !! Winner !! Runner-up\n|-\n| '''Cheetah Championship'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pba.com/Tournaments/FullStandings/1867 |title=Alka Seltzer Plus Cold Cheetah Championship - Full Standings |website=PBA.com |accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| Dec 16\n| Nov 3\u20137\n| Nov 10\n| Bill O\u2019Neill, USA\n| Mike Wolfe, USA\n|-\n| '''Viper Championship'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pba.com/Tournaments/FullStandings/1868 |title=WSOB Viper Championship - Fu