nts/Season/93 |title=PBA 2016 Season Schedule |website=PBA.com |accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pba.com/Tournaments/Details/2128 |title=GEICO World Series of Bowling VIII |website=PBA.com |accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n! Event !! Airdate !! Preliminary rounds !! Final round !! Winner !! Runner-up\n|-\n| '''Cheetah Championship'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pba.com/Tournaments/FullStandings/2130 |title=PBA Cheetah Championship presented by PBA Bowling Challenge Mobile Game - Full Standings |website=PBA.com |accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| Dec 18\n| Nov 29, Dec 6, 8\n| Dec 10\n| Mike Wolfe, USA\n| Darren Tang, USA\n|-\n| '''Chameleon Championship'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pba.com/Tournaments/FullStandings/2131 |title=PBA Chameleon Championship presented by HotelPlanner.com - Full Standings |website=PBA.com |accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| Dec 24\n| Nov 30, Dec 6, 8\n| Dec 10\n| Mitch Beasley, USA\n| AJ Johnson, USA\n|-\n| '''Scorpion Championship'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pba.com/Tournaments/FullStandings/2132 |title=PBA Scorpion Championship presented by Reno Tahoe USA - Full Standings |website=PBA.com |accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| Dec 25\n| Dec 1, 7\u20138\n| Dec 10\n| [[Tommy Jones (bowler)|Tommy Jones]], USA\n| BJ Moore, USA\n|-\n| '''Shark Championship'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pba.com/Tournaments/FullStandings/2133 |title=PBA Shark Championship - Full Standings |website=PBA.com |accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| Dec 25\n| Dec 2, 7\u20138\n| Dec 10\n| [[Fran\u00e7ois Lavoie]], Canada\n| Walter Ray Williams Jr., USA\n|-\n| '''PBA World Championship'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pba.com/articles/Indianae28099s-EJ-Tackett-Wins-PBA-World-Championship-for-First-Major-Fourth-2016-Title |title=Indiana\u2019s E.J. Tackett Wins PBA World Championship for First , Fourth 2016 Title |first=Bill |last=Vint |date=December 11, 2015 |accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</re