 2018, The Blue Stones signed a record contract with [[Entertainment One]], where they subsequently announced plans to re-release their debut LP ''Black Holes'' on October 26, 2018. They are set to tour the US with their Be My Fire Tour, which is their first official tour.<ref>{{cite web |title=Entertainment One Signs The Blue Stones |url=http://cashboxcanada.ca/9629/entertainment-one-signs-blue-stones |website=[[Cashbox (magazine)|Cashbox Canada]] |accessdate=30 October 2018 |date=3 August 2018}}</ref> In early January, The Blue Stones were nominated for the 2020 Juno Award in the category of Breakthrough Group of the Year. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.intelligencer.ca/news/local-news/windsor-rock-duo-the-blue-stones-nominated-for-juno-award/wcm/c6fdcd00-5e6b-4cd2-afef-6e9bd988c3b9|title=Windsor rock duo The Blue Stones nominated for Juno Award|last=Chen|first=Dalson|date=29 January 2020|website=The Intelligencer|url-status=live|access-date=February 9, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Members ==\n* Tarek Jafar \u2013 vocals, guitar\n* Justin Tessier \u2013 percussion, backing vocals\n\n== Discography ==\n=== Studio albums ===\n* ''[[Black Holes (album)|Black Holes]]'' (2015<ref>{{cite web |title=OUR TAKE: THE GRAVITATIONAL FLUX OF THE BLUE STONES\u2019 \u201cBLACK HOLES\u201d |url=https://atwoodmagazine.com/black-holes-the-blue-stones/ |website=atwoodmagazine.com |accessdate=6 January 2020}}</ref> (re-released 2018))\n\n=== Extended plays ===\n\n* ''The Blue Stones EP'' (2011)\n* ''How's That Sound?'' (2012)\n\n=== Singles ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Song\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! colspan=\"4\"| Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n! style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%\"|CAN<br>Rock<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/the-blue-stones/chart-history/CAR|title=Chart History: Canada Rock|work=Billboard|accessdate=January 6, 2020}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%\"|US<br>Air.<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboar